observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the:
(a) Management agreed to stop the inclusion of PPAs or expenditures which are not in accordance with DILG-DBM JMC No. 2017-1;
(b) Local Chief Executive agreed to direct the BAC, Technical Working Group and BAC Secretariat to submit the lacking documentary requirements to the Audit Team;
(c) Municipal Planning and Development Office (MPDO) and other concerned offices agreed to ensure that the appropriate PPAs which were not implemented in CY 2019 are fully delivered in the second year of implementation in order to deliver the needed socio-economic and environmental developments;
(d) Municipal Engineer, in coordination with the MPDO, agreed to observe the timeline of project completion and strictly monitor or supervise the implementation of project activities to avoid the incurrence of delays and to attain early the desired objectives of the projects; and
(e) Management agreed to observe the rule in accounting for obligations by taking up in the registries amounts committed to be paid by the agency once the related contracts between the Municipality and contractor were perfected.

We recommended and the LCE agreed to instruct the EXECOM and TWG to:
(a) comply with the provision of the JMC with respect to constitution of GFPS in accordance with Item 4.1.A.2 of the said law;
(b) consider utilizing all available resources to update the GAD database;
(c) submit, in writing, the changes in the DILG-approved GPB and secure an acknowledgement receipt of adjusted GPB from the DILG and fully integrate thereof in the annual budget and corresponding AIP of the Municipality;
(d) monitor the GAD PPAs and coordinate with concerned offices the implementation of GAD Plan and preparation of GAD AR;
(e) submit copy of Annual GAD Plan and Budget and GAD Accomplishment Report to the COA Audit Team within the prescribed deadline; and
(f) establish a GAD M&E Team to enhance, strengthen and maintain gender responsive monitoring and evaluation system on the outcomes of the LGU GAD policies, programs and projects.
